title: Subodh Bhetwal’s CV
text:
Computer Science Student.

isaac@applesdofall.org | My wikipedia page



Currently Computer Science Student in BYU-Idaho.



Machine learning algorithms (Decision Trees, Random Forests, Gradient Boosting, Neural Networks)
Data preprocessing and feature engineering with pandas and scikit-learn
Deep learning with TensorFlow and Keras
Graph algorithms and data structures (Dijkstra’s, Bellman-Ford, Huffman Encoding, Convex Hull)
Web development using React, JavaScript, HTML, and CSS
C# algorithm implementation with NUnit unit testing
Interactive visualizations using Lets-Plot and Matplotlib





Predictive modeling and model interpretability

Explainable AI and humanization of machine-generated content

Advanced data visualization techniques

Natural language processing and text generation

Optimization of graph and combinatorial algorithms





2021 – Present
Bachelor of Science in Computer Science, BYU-Idaho




2022 — Merit Scholarship, BYU-Idaho
2015 — Second Place in Interschool Soccer Tournamet, Aradhana Academy
2015 — First Place In Interschool Speling Bee Contest, Aradhana Academy





“Optimizing Housing Price Predictions with Ensemble Methods”*, Undergraduate Journal of Data Science, 2025

“Comparing Shortest-Path Algorithms in C#”*, GitHub Open Source Contributions, 2024

“Humanizing AI-Generated Text: Techniques and Trade-Offs”*, personal technical blog, 2025





Created pipelines and cleaned datasets using pandas

Implemented classic algorithms in C# with full NUnit testing

Developed plots and dashboards using Lets-Plot and Matplotlib

Contributed to GitHub repositories and collaborated on open-source projects
